components:
  - name: espagnol
    ingredients:
      - bacon
      - item: onion
        qty: 1
        unit: ea
        note: chopped
      - item: carrot
        note: finely chopped
      - item: celery
        note: finely chopped
      - item: butter
        mass: 50
      - item: flour
        note: roughly 1:1 with butter, a bit less
      - item: beef stock
        note: to cover
    steps:
      - start with bacon in pan, render some fat
      - add chopped onion and cook down slightly (not too brown) until most water gone
      - add finely chopped carrot and celery
      - add 50g butter once mirepoix is softened
      - add flour (forms roux with butter) once butter is melted
      - add beef stock and continue to cook down for like 15 mins
  - name: à l'orange
    ingredients:
      - item: espagnol sauce
        note: strained (max 1 big push through strainer, not too hard)
      - item: fresh orange juice
        note: fresh squeezed
      - item: salt
        optional: true
      - item: vinegar
        optional: true
        note: to taste
    steps:
      - strain espagnol (max 1 big push through strainer, not too hard)
      - add fresh squeezed orange juice
      - season with salt and vinegar to taste
      - cook duck mostly on crown at 150°C
notes: |
  Espagnol is a French brown sauce base. À l'orange is a variant using orange juice with duck.
